The paper deals with online algorithms for scheduling problems, specifically in the restricted assignment setting. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The use of rejection as a tool for optimization also relates to the area of online algorithms (cs.AL). The analysis of the algorithms involves probabilistic techniques, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics that could fit into multiple sub-categories, but the most likely ones are cs.DS, cs.AL, and cs.GT.
